  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0d85\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dbb 35 \u0dad\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "35 acres allotted to the villagers were given to an individual",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A group of people from Maliyadevapura village in Dimbulagala went to the Mahaweli Authority this morning to protest against the handing over of 35 acres of land given to them by an outsider.",
        "The protesters said that the person who had acquired the land had destroyed valuable trees and caused severe environmental damage and demanded that the decision of the Sri Lanka Mahaweli Authority to hand over the 35 acres of land allotted to them at the rate of 20 perches to one person be stopped immediately.",
        "The protesters said that the Sri Lanka Mahaweli Authority had demolished the boundary markers on the premises and if they did not comply with their demands, they would stage a massive protest in front of the Dimbulagala Mahaweli Divisional Office of the Sri Lanka Mahaweli Authority.",
        "When we inquired by telephone from the Dimbulagala Mahaweli Divisional Manager MGN Jayakody regarding the allegation made by the protesters, he stated that the land has been allocated by the Sri Lanka Mahaweli Authority for the chilli cultivation project and that a group of villagers will be selected to cultivate chillies in these lands. ."
      ],
